about.summary: a Python library for converting Creole wiki markup (aka wikicreole) for output on the web

name: creoleparser
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.7.4" %}

package:
  name: creoleparser
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/C/Creoleparser/Creoleparser-{{ version }}.zip
  sha256: 07af317e5c19e819130e01d8d698a741f05d69572642f5710b22b9f3630b45f3

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed --no-cache-dir -vvv"

requirements:
  build:
    - python <3
    - pip 
  run:
    - python <3
    - genshi >=0.4

test:
  imports:
    - creoleparser
    - creoleparser.core
    - creoleparser.dialects
    - creoleparser.elements

about:
  home: https://github.com/garrison/creoleparser
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  license_family: MIT
  summary: 'a Python library for converting Creole wiki markup (aka wikicreole) for output on the web'
  dev_url: https://github.com/garrison/creoleparser

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - pmlandwehr
